f(1) = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n(1+n)} =  \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left(\frac{1}{n}-\frac{1}{n+1}\right) = 1.
\frac{x}{n(1+nx^2)} = \frac{x}{n}-\frac{x^3}{1+nx^2},
f(x) = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left(\frac{x}{n}-\frac{x^3}{1+nx^2}\right).
n(1+nx^2) \ge 2n \sqrt{n}|x|.
